WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:53.300
Enter: Tony Tony Chopper

3
00:01:56.740 --> 00:01:58.300
Aren't you...

4
00:01:59.340 --> 00:02:00.510
peeking the wrong way?

5
00:02:07.590 --> 00:02:11.040
It's too late now...
and you're still clearly visible.

6
00:02:11.040 --> 00:02:12.360
Just what are you?

7
00:02:12.360 --> 00:02:15.320
Sh-Shut up, human!

8
00:02:15.920 --> 00:02:17.490
Also, how's your fever?

9
00:02:17.490 --> 00:02:18.490
It talked!

10
00:02:27.650 --> 00:02:29.340
Be quiet, Chopper!

11
00:02:38.860 --> 00:02:41.810
Your fever seems to have
come down a little, girl.

12
00:02:43.310 --> 00:02:44.020
Are ya happy?

13
00:02:49.520 --> 00:02:50.730
Who are you?

14
00:02:51.870 --> 00:02:54.950
Hmm, 38.2 degrees...
Not too shabby.

15
00:02:55.700 --> 00:03:00.700
I'm a doctor. Dr. Kureha.
Call me Doctorine.

16
00:03:01.170 --> 00:03:03.660
Doctor... Then I'm in the...

17
00:03:04.210 --> 00:03:05.750
The secret to my youth?

18
00:03:06.250 --> 00:03:07.750
No, I didn't ask that.

19
00:03:13.360 --> 00:03:16.390
You're right. You're in the castle
on top of the mountain.

20
00:03:16.390 --> 00:03:19.550
Then there were two others
with me, right?

21
00:03:19.550 --> 00:03:22.690
Yeah, they're sound asleep
in the next room.

22
00:03:22.690 --> 00:03:24.350
What tough guys...

23
00:03:26.100 --> 00:03:27.020
Look here.

24
00:03:28.230 --> 00:03:30.310
This was the cause.

25
00:03:30.310 --> 00:03:31.900
What... is this?

26
00:03:32.790 --> 00:03:35.330
You were bitten by a kestia.

27
00:03:35.330 --> 00:03:39.120
It's a poisonous tick that's only found
in hot and humid jungles.

28
00:03:39.120 --> 00:03:42.810
Once you're bitten by it,
bacteria enter your body

29
00:03:42.810 --> 00:03:46.250
and incubate for five days,
all while causing you pain.

30
00:03:47.680 --> 00:03:53.150
Fevers run above 40 degrees with
coinfection, myocarditis, arteritis, and cerebritis.

31
00:03:53.150 --> 00:03:57.760
Judging by the spread of infection,
I'd say you were bitten three days ago.

32
00:03:58.740 --> 00:04:01.650
You must have suffered
through immense pain.

33
00:04:01.650 --> 00:04:04.960
But, even without treatment,
it'd have ended after two more days.

34
00:04:04.960 --> 00:04:06.720
After two more days...?

35
00:04:06.730 --> 00:04:10.690
Yeah. After two more days,
you would have died.

36
00:04:10.690 --> 00:04:11.640
What?!

37
00:04:13.340 --> 00:04:15.090
It's called the "five-day disease."

38
00:04:15.090 --> 00:04:18.850
I had heard that kestias
died out a century ago,

39
00:04:18.850 --> 00:04:21.830
so it's good that I kept
the antibiotic just in case.

40
00:04:21.830 --> 00:04:24.170
Where did you guys come from?

41
00:04:24.170 --> 00:04:28.500
Were you walking around on a prehistoric
jungle island with your belly exposed?

42
00:04:30.070 --> 00:04:32.880
But that's just silly...

43
00:04:31.750 --> 00:04:32.880
Ah...

44
00:04:35.250 --> 00:04:37.420
That ring a bell?

45
00:04:37.420 --> 00:04:39.430
What a crazy girl...

46
00:04:39.850 --> 00:04:40.930
Now...

47
00:04:41.650 --> 00:04:45.790
Stay in bed. Your treatment
hasn't finished yet.

48
00:04:45.790 --> 00:04:49.330
Thanks for your help.
But my fever is much better already.

49
00:04:49.330 --> 00:04:51.230
I can heal on my own now, right?

50
00:04:51.230 --> 00:04:53.400
You're too optimistic.

51
00:04:53.400 --> 00:04:58.030
This disease normally takes
a minimum of ten days to fully treat.

52
00:04:58.030 --> 00:05:03.200
Unless, of course, you want it to
flare up again and kill you this time.

53
00:05:03.200 --> 00:05:07.100
Even with my medicine,
you'll have to rest at least three days.

54
00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:07.790
What...?

55
00:05:07.790 --> 00:05:09.500
I can't stay here for three days!

56
00:05:10.160 --> 00:05:11.830
Vivi must reach Alabasta soon!

57
00:05:14.670 --> 00:05:18.360
A patient only leaves
my care one of two ways:

58
00:05:19.800 --> 00:05:21.250
cured or dead.

59
00:05:21.250 --> 00:05:22.640
You're not leaving here.

60
00:05:50.480 --> 00:05:53.060
He climbed this mountain
with his bare hands?!

61
00:05:53.060 --> 00:05:55.790
This 5,000-meter-high Drum Rock?!

62
00:05:57.760 --> 00:06:00.160
Nearly his entire body is frostbitten.

63
00:06:00.160 --> 00:06:02.380
What was he thinking
dressing like this?

64
00:06:02.380 --> 00:06:04.470
Throw him in a warm bath immediately.

65
00:06:05.170 --> 00:06:10.050
This guy's bleeding badly.
Six broken ribs and a spinal fissure.

66
00:06:10.050 --> 00:06:11.430
Can I operate on him?

67
00:06:13.060 --> 00:06:18.030
This girl's the most critical.
She's barely alive.

68
00:06:18.030 --> 00:06:22.360
Chopper, ready some phenicol,
cardiotonic, and tialcillin.

69
00:06:22.360 --> 00:06:24.190
Does she have an infection?

70
00:06:24.190 --> 00:06:27.030
Yeah, and the pathogen
isn't from this island.

71
00:06:33.890 --> 00:06:37.850
Don't worry. I'll make both that
bleeding kid and this girl all better.

72
00:06:37.850 --> 00:06:38.880
You can relax.

73
00:06:41.190 --> 00:06:43.380
Th-They're my f-friends...!

74
00:06:49.190 --> 00:06:51.920
I get the picture. I'll help them.

75
00:06:51.920 --> 00:06:53.890
Chopper! Let's begin treatment!

76
00:07:00.350 --> 00:07:02.860
Th-They're my f-friends...!

77
00:07:04.250 --> 00:07:05.600
I'm...

78
00:07:06.860 --> 00:07:09.080
I'm hungry...

79
00:07:13.770 --> 00:07:15.220
Meat...

80
00:07:19.500 --> 00:07:23.200
Venison stew needs to be cooked
in a pot for three hours,

81
00:07:23.200 --> 00:07:25.380
then the meat
becomes properly tender.

82
00:07:28.020 --> 00:07:30.140
Venison...!

83
00:07:39.100 --> 00:07:42.730
Ahhhh! Help!

84
00:07:44.720 --> 00:07:45.700
Wait, meat!

85
00:07:51.360 --> 00:07:53.490
Wait, Luffy! I'll cook him for you!

86
00:08:01.620 --> 00:08:02.860
Nami?!

87
00:08:02.860 --> 00:08:03.550
Nami!

88
00:08:03.890 --> 00:08:05.340
You got better?

89
00:08:05.340 --> 00:08:06.630
Yeah, thanks.

90
00:08:06.630 --> 00:08:10.140
Okay, then! I'll make a nutritious
venison dish for Nami!

91
00:08:13.480 --> 00:08:16.310
– Wait!
– Wait!

92
00:08:18.490 --> 00:08:21.620
I'm surprised they can
already move around.

93
00:08:21.620 --> 00:08:25.190
What's that talking stuffed deer
with the blue nose?

94
00:08:25.190 --> 00:08:26.780
You're asking me what he is?

95
00:08:26.780 --> 00:08:28.450
Don't run away, meat!

96
00:08:28.450 --> 00:08:31.460
Wait, Luffy! I'm telling you
not to eat it yet!

97
00:08:34.740 --> 00:08:36.290
Stop it, humans!

98
00:08:36.290 --> 00:08:40.170
His name is Chopper.
He's just a reindeer with a blue nose.

99
00:08:41.690 --> 00:08:43.630
Reindeer don't talk.

100
00:08:43.630 --> 00:08:45.630
S-Stop it, you jerks!

101
00:08:45.630 --> 00:08:49.090
S-Stop it!

102
00:08:46.320 --> 00:08:49.090
He's a regular reindeer
that just happened to...

103
00:08:49.590 --> 00:08:51.090
Just happened to...?

104
00:08:54.310 --> 00:08:56.820
I'm not food!

105
00:08:59.460 --> 00:09:02.900
...eat the Human-Human Fruit.

106
00:09:02.900 --> 00:09:04.360
The Human-Human Fruit...

107
00:09:04.930 --> 00:09:06.280
One of the devil fruits...

108
00:09:07.860 --> 00:09:13.790
Yeah. He's become
a reindeer with human abilities.

109
00:09:14.450 --> 00:09:16.450
Rats! Rats!

110
00:09:17.070 --> 00:09:22.210
And I taught him everything
I know about medicine.

111
00:09:25.630 --> 00:09:28.050
Oh, it's already over?

112
00:09:32.890 --> 00:09:34.970
What a disappointing bunch.

113
00:09:36.600 --> 00:09:38.390
– What was that?!
– Amazing...

114
00:09:40.560 --> 00:09:41.770
Amazing...

115
00:09:42.730 --> 00:09:46.770
All right! Good job, Zoro!
Just as I instructed!

116
00:09:48.900 --> 00:09:50.360
Let's find Dalton!

117
00:09:50.360 --> 00:09:51.360
Yeah!

118
00:09:53.740 --> 00:09:55.070
Thank you!

119
00:09:57.030 --> 00:09:58.990
Hurry up! Dig everywhere!

120
00:10:00.500 --> 00:10:03.670
So, what's all this fuss about?

121
00:10:03.670 --> 00:10:06.590
I'll explain later! Let's help them!

122
00:10:06.960 --> 00:10:09.550
Dalton! Please be alive!

123
00:10:20.060 --> 00:10:23.060
Join my crew!
Please, old lady!

124
00:10:23.060 --> 00:10:25.020
We need a doctor on our ship!

125
00:10:25.020 --> 00:10:28.520
Luffy! You said that's
your name, right?

126
00:10:28.520 --> 00:10:29.940
Yeah, I did, old la–

127
00:10:30.360 --> 00:10:33.400
Watch... what you say!

128
00:10:35.820 --> 00:10:40.040
I'm still in my youthful 130s.

129
00:10:40.040 --> 00:10:42.040
Whoa. What an incredible old hag.

130
00:10:44.420 --> 00:10:46.790
Are you asking me to be a pirate?

131
00:10:47.710 --> 00:10:51.800
Don't be ridiculous!
It'd be a waste of my glorious time.

132
00:10:51.800 --> 00:10:54.260
I'm not interested in the sea.

133
00:10:55.050 --> 00:10:58.100
Who cares? Let's go
on an adventure, old lady!

134
00:10:58.390 --> 00:11:02.060
Hey now. I just told you
to watch what you say, didn't I?

135
00:11:02.890 --> 00:11:04.770
So they're pirates...

136
00:11:11.690 --> 00:11:14.530
Wait, meat!

137
00:11:12.740 --> 00:11:14.530
Wait!

138
00:11:17.740 --> 00:11:19.660
Hold it, you brats!

139
00:11:27.170 --> 00:11:28.630
Wait!

140
00:11:28.630 --> 00:11:32.210
Hold on, Nami! I'll cook
a nutritious reindeer dish!

141
00:11:33.590 --> 00:11:37.340
Before that, I'll eat you guys!

142
00:11:37.720 --> 00:11:39.050
– The old hag!
– The old hag!

143
00:11:39.050 --> 00:11:40.890
Where the heck did she come from?!

144
00:11:41.470 --> 00:11:41.720
She's coming!

145
00:11:41.720 --> 00:11:42.010
She's coming! She's coming!

146
00:11:42.010 --> 00:11:42.310
She's coming! She's coming!
She's coming!

147
00:11:42.310 --> 00:11:43.470
She's coming! She's coming!
She's coming! She's coming!

148
00:11:47.730 --> 00:11:51.270
Forget the food. I just want
some peace and quiet.

149
00:11:57.490 --> 00:12:00.740
Snow? Even though
we're inside the castle...?

150
00:12:01.450 --> 00:12:02.200
So cold...!

151
00:12:05.160 --> 00:12:07.830
I'll close the door.

152
00:12:06.160 --> 00:12:07.830
Hey! Stay in bed!

153
00:12:10.210 --> 00:12:12.210
You still have a fever!

154
00:12:12.210 --> 00:12:15.710
I don't. It seems like
it's pretty much gone.

155
00:12:15.710 --> 00:12:17.220
Looks like I lost them...

156
00:12:17.220 --> 00:12:18.180
Even so, no!

157
00:12:18.930 --> 00:12:22.970
Doctorine's medicine makes
the fever go away quickly.

158
00:12:22.970 --> 00:12:25.680
But the kestia's bacteria
still remain in your body.

159
00:12:26.310 --> 00:12:29.400
You need to have your
antibiotic shot and stay in bed.

160
00:12:30.650 --> 00:12:31.770
Thank you.

161
00:12:32.940 --> 00:12:35.320
You've been taking care of me, right?

162
00:12:35.820 --> 00:12:36.690
Sh...

163
00:12:38.070 --> 00:12:39.570
Shut up!

164
00:12:39.860 --> 00:12:43.330
I don't wanna be thanked by a human!

165
00:12:44.580 --> 00:12:47.450
Don't mock me! You jerk!

166
00:12:47.450 --> 00:12:49.000
Don't be silly, you dummy!

167
00:12:50.080 --> 00:12:52.250
Seriously, don't be so...

168
00:12:52.250 --> 00:12:55.050
He's quite the open book, isn't he?

169
00:12:59.630 --> 00:13:03.510
This castle is strange.
It's cold and there's snow inside.

170
00:13:03.510 --> 00:13:04.680
Oh...?

171
00:13:07.560 --> 00:13:08.850
Ahhh! It's cold!

172
00:13:08.850 --> 00:13:11.020
You keep taking
your sweet time with that!

173
00:13:16.860 --> 00:13:18.030
Look at this.

174
00:13:24.620 --> 00:13:27.040
There's snow everywhere in the castle.

175
00:13:29.200 --> 00:13:32.040
The doors for the unused rooms
are all frozen, too.

176
00:13:48.270 --> 00:13:49.930
Hold it! Hold it! Hold it!

177
00:13:56.520 --> 00:14:00.190
Wh-Wh-Whoa! Hey, Luffy!
Stop asking that old bag to join us!

178
00:14:00.190 --> 00:14:03.280
She's not a doctor, she's a murderer!

179
00:14:08.290 --> 00:14:10.000
Are you guys pirates?

180
00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:10.870
Yes...

181
00:14:12.080 --> 00:14:13.250
R-Real ones?

182
00:14:13.250 --> 00:14:14.670
Real ones.

183
00:14:14.670 --> 00:14:16.250
You have a flag with a skull?

184
00:14:16.250 --> 00:14:19.590
It's attached to our ship.
Are you interested in pirates?

185
00:14:19.920 --> 00:14:22.050
No! You idiot! No!

186
00:14:22.880 --> 00:14:24.050
You idiot!

187
00:14:26.180 --> 00:14:28.010
Okay. Okay. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

188
00:14:29.970 --> 00:14:32.020
But... then...

189
00:14:33.060 --> 00:14:33.980
wanna come too?

190
00:14:34.400 --> 00:14:35.730
What?!

191
00:14:35.730 --> 00:14:38.190
To the sea! Why don't
you come with us?

192
00:14:38.570 --> 00:14:39.570
Hm?

193
00:14:39.570 --> 00:14:41.900
If you do, it'll really help me out!

194
00:14:41.900 --> 00:14:45.570
With a doctor, I won't have to
stay here for three days, right?

195
00:14:45.570 --> 00:14:47.240
On top of that, on our ship, we–

196
00:14:47.240 --> 00:14:48.830
D-Don't be ridiculous!

197
00:14:49.240 --> 00:14:50.700
I'm a reindeer!

198
00:14:50.700 --> 00:14:53.660
There's no way I can
stay with humans!

199
00:14:55.620 --> 00:14:59.170
To start with, don't you
get scared when you see me?

200
00:14:59.170 --> 00:15:03.630
I'm a reindeer, but I stand
on two legs and I even speak.

201
00:15:04.840 --> 00:15:07.760
What? Are you trying to scare me?

202
00:15:10.180 --> 00:15:11.390
My nose is blue, too...

203
00:15:21.610 --> 00:15:22.820
There you are!

204
00:15:23.360 --> 00:15:24.610
Reindeer!

205
00:15:26.030 --> 00:15:27.320
– Wait!
– Wait!

206
00:15:32.740 --> 00:15:34.330
Those brats sure are quick.

207
00:15:37.540 --> 00:15:39.750
I don't like it, girl.

208
00:15:39.750 --> 00:15:40.750
What?

209
00:15:40.750 --> 00:15:44.510
Who gave you permission to tempt
the reindeer behind my back?

210
00:15:44.510 --> 00:15:48.140
Oh? Do I need permission
to make a move on a man?

211
00:15:49.600 --> 00:15:53.220
No, you don't. If you wanna
take him, go right ahead.

212
00:15:53.220 --> 00:15:55.810
But it won't be easy.

213
00:15:56.230 --> 00:16:01.230
He has a scar in his heart—
a big scar that even I can't cure.

214
00:16:01.230 --> 00:16:05.320
The moment he came into this world,
his herd and his parents abandoned him.

215
00:16:05.320 --> 00:16:06.070
What?

216
00:16:07.320 --> 00:16:09.660
It was all because of his blue nose.

217
00:16:09.990 --> 00:16:14.870
He always walked at the very back
of the herd all by himself

218
00:16:14.870 --> 00:16:17.120
even though he was
just a newborn child.

219
00:16:17.460 --> 00:16:23.090
After he ate a devil fruit,
he was treated like a true monster.

220
00:16:35.560 --> 00:16:38.640
The other reindeer drove him
out of the herd.

221
00:16:39.190 --> 00:16:43.820
There was no way he could ever
go back to being an ordinary reindeer.

222
00:16:44.320 --> 00:16:47.400
Still, he wanted friends...

223
00:16:47.400 --> 00:16:50.320
So he went down to a village,
this time as a human.

224
00:16:51.070 --> 00:16:53.620
Hey! What's that creature?

225
00:16:53.620 --> 00:16:57.870
But his figure wasn't
exactly human, either.

226
00:16:57.870 --> 00:17:01.080
For some reason,
his nose also remained blue.

227
00:17:01.080 --> 00:17:02.580
It must be a yeti!

228
00:17:02.580 --> 00:17:05.630
It's dangerous!
Get the children inside quickly!

229
00:17:07.380 --> 00:17:09.050
A gun! Bring me a gun!

230
00:17:09.050 --> 00:17:10.090
Shoot it dead!

231
00:17:10.090 --> 00:17:11.430
You damn monster!

232
00:17:11.430 --> 00:17:13.050
Go away!

233
00:17:30.570 --> 00:17:33.200
He didn't know what was wrong,

234
00:17:33.200 --> 00:17:36.160
nor did he know what to blame.

235
00:17:36.410 --> 00:17:38.250
You damn monster!

236
00:17:38.250 --> 00:17:40.120
You damn monster!

237
00:17:40.120 --> 00:17:44.710
All he wanted were friends,
but he was called a monster...

238
00:17:45.170 --> 00:17:47.800
He was no longer a reindeer.

239
00:17:47.800 --> 00:17:49.130
He wasn't a human, either.

240
00:17:50.970 --> 00:17:55.350
And so, he had to live alone.

241
00:17:56.390 --> 00:18:00.060
Can you guys heal
the scar in his heart?

242
00:18:02.480 --> 00:18:07.070
Hey, Luffy. Look at that door
at the front entrance. It's wide open.

243
00:18:11.990 --> 00:18:13.360
No wonder it's cold.

244
00:18:13.360 --> 00:18:15.200
In any case, let's close this door.

245
00:18:15.200 --> 00:18:18.040
Otherwise, we might as well
be out in the snow.

246
00:18:18.490 --> 00:18:21.370
Hey! Stop it!
Don't touch that door!

247
00:18:24.080 --> 00:18:27.000
Never mind him. Let's close it,
or we'll freeze to death.

248
00:18:27.000 --> 00:18:27.840
Definitely.

249
00:18:28.340 --> 00:18:30.800
Hey! Didn't I tell you to...

250
00:18:31.210 --> 00:18:32.380
stop it?!

251
00:18:37.720 --> 00:18:41.180
What's with him? Why is he angry?

252
00:18:43.190 --> 00:18:45.900
Hey, Luffy. Come over here.

253
00:18:52.610 --> 00:18:53.700
Look up there.

254
00:19:02.450 --> 00:19:06.540
They're snowbird hatchlings.
So, if we close the door, they'll fall.

255
00:19:07.170 --> 00:19:09.500
That's why they can't close it.

256
00:19:20.930 --> 00:19:22.640
– It's cold!
– It's cold!

257
00:19:24.940 --> 00:19:26.400
Hold on a sec.

258
00:19:26.400 --> 00:19:27.440
What is it?

259
00:19:26.730 --> 00:19:27.440
Ah!

260
00:19:28.150 --> 00:19:30.270
Didn't he talk just now?!

261
00:19:30.690 --> 00:19:33.320
And come to think of it,
he was standing on two legs.

262
00:19:35.610 --> 00:19:37.530
– He's a monster!
– He's a monster!

263
00:19:39.660 --> 00:19:41.490
Wh-What the heck is that?

264
00:19:42.160 --> 00:19:44.200
He's walking on two legs...

265
00:19:44.200 --> 00:19:45.210
He's a reindeer...

266
00:19:45.210 --> 00:19:45.910
He's fluffy...

267
00:19:45.910 --> 00:19:46.870
He's short...

268
00:19:46.870 --> 00:19:48.920
He becomes big...

269
00:19:48.920 --> 00:19:50.960
– And he's a monster!
– And he's a monster!

270
00:20:05.350 --> 00:20:07.890
What a cool guy! I like him!

271
00:20:08.190 --> 00:20:12.110
Sanji! Let's have him join us!
